WEBVTT
1
00:00:01.744 --> 00:00:04.462
You can push your Git repository to different Git

2
00:00:04.462 --> 00:00:07.714
services like GitHub or Azure DevOps.

3
00:00:07.714 --> 00:00:10.432
If you want to handle pull requests for these

4
00:00:10.432 --> 00:00:12.724
services directly in Visual Studio,

5
00:00:12.724 --> 00:00:16.714
you need to install the corresponding Visual Studio extension.

6
00:00:16.714 --> 00:00:20.744
For GitHub, you can use the GitHub extension for Visual Studio.

7
00:00:20.744 --> 00:00:26.694
You'll find more information about this extension on visualstudio.github .com.

8
00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:31.694
For Azure DevOps, you can install the Pull Requests for Visual Studio extension,

9
00:00:31.694 --> 00:00:34.784
and this is exactly what we do now in a demonstration.

10
00:00:34.784 --> 00:00:38.081
You will learn how to install the Pull Requests for Visual

11
00:00:38.081 --> 00:00:41.714
Studio extension to create pull requests for our Azure Repo

12
00:00:41.714 --> 00:00:43.724
directly in Visual Studio.

13
00:00:43.724 --> 00:00:46.764
Let's switch to Visual Studio.

14
00:00:46.764 --> 00:00:48.344
Here in Visual Studio,

15
00:00:48.344 --> 00:00:53.744
let's go to the Extensions menu and let's select here Extensions and Updates.

16
00:00:53.744 --> 00:00:56.774
Now let's click on the left side on Online.

17
00:00:56.774 --> 00:00:59.784
Here is the GitHub extension for Visual Studio.

18
00:00:59.784 --> 00:01:04.764
Now let's use the search box here and let's type in Pull Requests.

19
00:01:04.764 --> 00:01:08.774
And here is now the Pull Requests for Visual Studio extension.

20
00:01:08.774 --> 00:01:11.764
Let's click the Download button.

21
00:01:11.764 --> 00:01:14.774
Now you can see the changes will be scheduled.

22
00:01:14.774 --> 00:01:18.230
The modifications will begin when all Microsoft

23
00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:20.724
Visual Studio windows are closed.

24
00:01:20.724 --> 00:01:23.694
So let's close this Visual Studio window.

25
00:01:23.694 --> 00:01:24.754
Now the installer starts,

26
00:01:24.754 --> 00:01:27.271
and now I get this dialog to install the Pull

27
00:01:27.271 --> 00:01:29.754
Requests for Visual Studio extension.

28
00:01:29.754 --> 00:01:32.774
Let's click on Modify to install this extension.

29
00:01:32.774 --> 00:01:36.007
Now the installation is complete and the Pull Requests for

30
00:01:36.007 --> 00:01:37.784
Visual Studio extension was installed.

31
00:01:37.784 --> 00:01:46.000
Let's close this dialog, and let's create a pull request in Visual Studio in the next clip.

